result.execSummary:
The defendant Kayla N Luebke was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Neglecting a Child (Specified Harm Did Not Occur), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.21(2).
  • Neglecting a Child (Specified Harm Did Not Occur), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.21(2).
  • Neglecting a Child (Specified Harm Did Not Occur), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 948.21(2).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

[ma] Case called at 9:47 AM 
Defendant Kayla N Luebke in court.  Attorney Jonathan K McDonell in court for Kayla N Luebke.  Attorney Brookellen Teuber in court for State of Wisconsin. 
ADA Teuber verifies victim rights compliance, submits victim impact statement. 

Maximum penalties are recited; Constitutional rights are reviewed; pleas of " GUILTY " entered on Counts #3, #4, and #5; factual basis stipulated.  The Court accepts the pleas, finds the Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads-in and dismisses Counts #1 and #2.

Sentencing recommendations/ arguments given by Counsel 

On Counts #3, #4, and #5, the Court withholds sentence and places the Defendant on Probation for 2 years, with conditions:
--to serve 30 days in the Jefferson County Jail, with work-release privileges, to commence FORTHWITH [Upon Clerk inquiry, conditional jail is on each count, since it is a condition of probation, the Court is not voicing whether it is consecutive or concurrent.]

--to undergo AODA assessment and follow through with recommended treatment per Agent
--comply with all existing Family and Children's Court orders
--to undergo any other assessment, treatment, or counseling per Agent
--random drug and/or alcohol screening
--maintain absolute sobriety
--no presence in bars, taverns, or liquor stores
--no possession of firearms
--to comply with DNA sample provision 

Separate from the conditions of Probation, the Court orders payment of costs, fees and surcharges through the Clerk of Courts Office. [Clerk calculates this total to be:$1329] The Court grants the Defendant sixty days to either pay the amount in full or to establish a payment plan with the Clerk of Courts Office.  Non-payment will result in   days in Jail with Huber privileges, consecutive.  
 

Days credit for time already served:  3  days
